    {
        "content": "<p>A nice demonstration of backpassing as well :)</p>",
        "id": 298628889,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1663088723
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>folks - is the platform we used for the session supposed to be available in the current nightly release for mac os? I've downloaded the last two builds and there is only \"hello-world\" in the examples folder:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/releases\">https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/releases</a></p>",
        "id": 298648992,
        "sender_full_name": "Georges Boris",
        "timestamp": 1663095864
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, the releases only contain the hello world platform - you need to clone the roc repo to get the other examples, one of which is what we used</p>",
        "id": 298659632,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1663099653
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>However, perhaps now/soon we should bundle the example CLI platform with the releases!</p>",
        "id": 298659784,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1663099700
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Eventually it won't be necessary, when any published platform is available as a remote package via package manager</p>",
        "id": 298659913,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1663099760
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I actually think it's probably better for now to encourage people to clone the repo to get the CLI platform, since it's being actively updated; otherwise you'll probably get the one version you downloaded with whenever you happened to get Nightly, and won't have the convenient <code>git pull</code> to update it</p>",
        "id": 298664617,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1663101916
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If they aren't building from source they may have to update their version of the compiler anyway to support newer versions of the platform.</p>",
        "id": 298668512,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1663103668
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Interesting</p>",
        "id": 298668601,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1663103724
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>true!</p>",
        "id": 298676568,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1663107845
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>got it! so - I know this is getting off-topic but just so we can finish the thread: when building from source via <code>cargo build --release</code> where would I find the build result similar to what one would see on nightly builds?</p>",
        "id": 298753656,
        "sender_full_name": "Georges Boris",
        "timestamp": 1663155928
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the roc binary would be in the folder target/release/<br>\nIf you move the roc binary somewhere else, you should also copy along the lib folder (also in target/release/)</p>",
        "id": 298754133,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1663156075
    }
